Create Staging Database in SQL Server

The following steps will help you to create a Staging database.

  1. Open Microsoft SQL Server Management Studio.
  2. Right Click on Database ==> Click on New Database.
  3. New Database dialog box appears ==> Then, give a name for your new database.
  4. Click Ok to create a new database.
  5. Click on the plus sign next to the database on object explorer ==> Located newly created database. If you don't see the newly created database, then Right Click on database ==> Click on refresh from the popup dialog box.
